        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-16 17:04:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYes, it's nothing weird. This commit is supposed to fail in this case. \n\nThink about it. The config is set to follow current branch in subproject. You have just created a new one (locally) for example ABC. So git tries to find branch ABC also in subproject repo but it obviously does not exist.",
        "patchset_number": 1
